---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import FeatureBlock from '../components/FeatureBlock.astro';
import CalloutBand from '../components/CalloutBand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Paws on Longmeadow">
  <Hero
    title="It Started With Ollie"
    subtitle="Some businesses start with a business plan. Ours started with a road trip."
  />

  <FeatureBlock heading="From one dog to many">
    <p>
      In 2017, Gus and Marian closed on their first home, a garrison colonial on a quiet street in
      Sharon with the big yard they had always dreamed about. Weeks later they drove to Virginia for
      a puppy named Ollie. They didn't have a plan yet. They had Ollie, and that turned out to be
      enough.
    </p>
    <p>
      When a friend needed help with his dog, watching Ollie play alongside another dog in a safe,
      familiar place was unlike anything they had seen. The next day, Gus opened a Rover profile. For
      years it ran quietly and part-time, word spreading the way it does in a neighborhood. In 2024,
      Gus left his career as a creative project manager and committed to it full-time.
    </p>
  </FeatureBlock>

  <FeatureBlock heading="This is our home" ctaLabel="See the space" ctaHref="/our-home">
    <p>
      That is not a tagline. Paws on Longmeadow is not a facility or a kennel. It is the home where
      Gus and Marian live, where their kids are growing up, and where Ollie, now nine, holds court
      from his favorite spot. When your dog stays with us, they are sleeping where we sleep and
      playing where our family plays.
    </p>
  </FeatureBlock>

  <FeatureBlock heading="The people behind the paws">
    <p>
      <strong>Gus</strong> ran creative projects for years before making this his full-time life in
      2024. That shows in the attention to detail and the consistency he works to give every family.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Marian</strong> is the heartbeat of the day-to-day. She greets nearly every dog who
      walks through the door and says goodbye to each one. She handles some walks, drives dogs home,
      and takes the photos and videos, a fact that becomes obvious the moment you see them.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Their two boys</strong> have grown up in the middle of all of this. They have never
      known a home without dogs in it. The pups know it too.
    </p>
  </FeatureBlock>

  <FeatureBlock heading="Why families choose us">
    <ul>
      <li>We are a home, not a facility. Your dog lives with a family, not in a run.</li>
      <li>Someone is always here. There is a familiar face in the house.</li>
      <li>We have been doing this since 2018, long before it was a business.</li>
      <li>Small by design, so every dog gets attention.</li>
      <li>Ollie approves every guest. That is not a joke. He is very particular.</li>
    </ul>
  </FeatureBlock>

  <CalloutBand
    heading="Come meet us"
    text="The best way to understand this place is to experience it."
    ctaLabel="Request a Meet & Greet"
    ctaHref="/request-a-meet-and-greet"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  ul { display: grid; gap: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; color: var(--ink); }
</style>
